post_text: Today was our last day offering free meals to the children of our community under the Summer Eats program. We would like to thank all of our Food Service workers and volunteers for making this possible and also thank the community for participating in record numbers. We thoroughly enjoyed the opportunity to serve you these last several months at our 5 remote sites and wish everyone a great start to the new school year. And don't forget, free meals will be offered to all children starting next Tuesday, through December 31, 2020. More information on how to sign up will be posted shortly.

post_text:
A note from our Food Services Director!
>>>>>>> master

Hello All!
As the summer comes to an end and the start of the school year fast approaches we will continue to provide meals for students in the district. As you may have heard, the USDA is extending free meals to all students until December 31st. The State of Massachusetts will be providing more clarity on Thursday, 9/10, to determine if our district qualifies. A Google form will be released this week for meal ordering for the opening of school. We appreciate your patience and look forward to your participation in the SEBRSD Meals program!

If you have any questions please feel free to email me at pulverb@sebrsd.org or give me a call at 774-200-7162.

Thank You,
Brianne Pulver
SEBRSD Food Services Director
text:
A note from our Food Services Director!

Hello All!
As the summer comes to an end and the start of the school year fast approaches we will continue to provide meals for students in the district. As you may have heard, the USDA is extending free meals to all students until December 31st. The State of Massachusetts will be providing more clarity on Thursday, 9/10, to determine if our district qualifies. A Google form will be released this week for meal ordering for the opening of school. We appreciate your patience and look forward to your participation in the SEBRSD Meals program!

If you have any questions please feel free to email me at pulverb@sebrsd.org or give me a call at 774-200-7162.

Thank You,
Brianne Pulver
SEBRSD Food Services Director

Here are some questions and answers from last week's parent/student meetings.

What are the summer reading assignments?
Read Stamped. We have a copy for everyone. Go into the Google Classroom (4allky3), and do the reflection questions and the creative project. They count for two English test grades in the first quarter.

When will my student get a schedule?
We mailed them out a few weeks ago, so call us at 508-885-8505 to find out if we have your correct address and to get a copy of the schedule.

If I am taking a virtual high school class, will i have to log in with a teacher, or do i work on it on my own time?
How will Virtual High School classes work in the block schedule?
Email Ms.â€¦

Spencer Police Department
May 26 at 9:44 AM Â·

Wearing of Facial Covering
There have been postings on social media that Police will not enforce the STATE mandatory mask order. Nothing could be further from the truth. That said, our goal of enforcement is to educate and promote compliance first. In this pursuit, Spencer Officers are carrying a supply of complementary masks. Should these passive measures fail a $300 bylaw violation will be issued. Anyone failing to pay a bylaw violation will end up before a Judge. So please, do the right thing.

April is National O.T. Month â€“ So meet your O.T.â€™s

If you havenâ€™t met us yet â€“ we would like to introduce ourselves.

My name is Pamela Higgins. I am a licensed Registered Occupational Therapist. I have enjoyed working with the students and teachers as part of the district school family for 32 years.

My name is Wendy Ryan and I am a licensed COTA who has been a dedicated member of our school family for the past 19 years. I have enjoyed helping the children here be the most successful and independent students they can be...

We both feel honored to be able to serve the children and their families, along with the wonderful and amazing staff in all schools of the Spencer and East Brookfield communities. #Progress #Unity #Knowledge

My name is Pamela Higgins. I am a licensed Registered Occupational Therapist. I have enjoyed working with the students and teachers as part of the district school family for 32 years.

My name is Wendy Ryan and I am a licensed COTA who has been a dedicated member of our school family for the past 19 years. I have enjoyed helping the children here be the most successful and independent students they can be...

April 8, 2019 at 8:44 PM Â·

April is National O.T. Month â€“ So meet your O.T.â€™s

If you havenâ€™t met us yet â€“ we would like to introduce ourselves.

My name is Pamela Higgins. I am a licensed Registered Occupational Therapist. I have enjoyed working with the students and teachers as part of the district school family for 32 years.

My name is Wendy Ryan and I am a licensed COTA who has been a dedicated member of our school family for the past 19 years. I have enjoyed helping the children here be the most successful and independent students they can be...

We both feel honored to be able to serve the children and their families, along with the wonderful and amazing staff in all schools of the Spencer and East Brookfield communities. #Progress #Unity #Knowledge

post_text: How many can you find tomorrow? #WireVillageRocks
shared_text:
Wire Village School - Spencer
April 9 at 9:13 AM Â·

Social Distancing Egg Hunt
April 10, 2020
11:00am-12:15pm
(There will be 28 Wire Village staff members stationed around Spencer in their decorated cars. How many can you find?)

The Easter bunny was sad, and a little bit scared.
Since the schools were all closed, life had gotten quite weird.

To keep everyone healthy, he stayed home every day.
He was careful to keep at least six feet away.

But he still wanted Easter. He still wanted to give.
So he plotted and planned, then began to get active.

He hopped all through town, leaving signs, eggs, and smiles
as a reminder this shutdown is just for a while.

He first stopped for groceries at two different stores
to get little surprises to leaveâ€¦
